questions.question:
Assume two processes P0 and P1, each execute a critical section CS and need to use two semaphores S1 and S2 to implement mutual exclusion over the CS. Complete the following algorithms so that deadlock will be impossible.

Initial values for S1 and S2: S1=___; S2=___;

Alg for P0:          Alg for P1:
wait(___);           wait(___);
wait(___);           wait(___);
CS;                  CS;
signal(___);         signal(___);
signal(___);         signal(___);

questions.answer:
Initial values: S1 = 1; S2 = 1;

Alg for P0:          Alg for P1:
wait(S1);            wait(S1);
wait(S2);            wait(S2);
CS;                  CS;
signal(S2);          signal(S2);
signal(S1);          signal(S1);

Aciklama:
- S1 ve S2 binary semaphore (baslangic degeri 1)
- HER IKI SUREC semafollari AYNI SIRADA alir: once S1, sonra S2
- Ayni sira = circular wait olusmas! = deadlock imkansiz
- Signal'lar ters sirada: once S2, sonra S1 (LIFO)

DIKKAT - YANLIS COZUM (Deadlock olusur):
P0: wait(S1);wait(S2) ve P1: wait(S2);wait(S1)
Bu durumda P0 S1'i alir, P1 S2'yi alir, ikisi de birbirini bekler -> DEADLOCK!
